<!-- Hero -->
<section style="padding-top:140px;padding-bottom:60px;background:linear-gradient(180deg,#FFFFFF 0%,#F7F9FC 100%);">
  <div style="max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 24px;">
    <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      <span style="background:rgba(5,199,147,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(5,199,147,0.2);border-radius:9999px;padding:4px 12px;font-size:0.72rem;font-weight:700;color:#05C793;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.06em;">AI Strategy</span>
      <span style="background:rgba(124,58,237,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(124,58,237,0.2);border-radius:9999px;padding:4px 12px;font-size:0.72rem;font-weight:700;color:#a855f7;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.06em;">Cybersecurity SaaS</span>
      <span style="background:rgba(96,165,250,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.2);border-radius:9999px;padding:4px 12px;font-size:0.72rem;font-weight:700;color:#60a5fa;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.06em;">MEA &amp; APAC</span>
    </div>
    <h1 style="font-size:clamp(1.8rem,4vw,2.8rem);font-weight:900;color:#12172B;line-height:1.2;margin-bottom:1.5rem;letter-spacing:-0.02em;">How a Global Cybersecurity SaaS Went From Fragmented AI Initiatives to a Unified Strategy — and $1.2M in Attributable Pipeline</h1>
    <p style="color:#5B6478;font-size:1rem;line-height:1.75;max-width:720px;">Disconnected regional campaigns. No shared intelligence layer. Enterprise conversion stuck below target. The problem was not the product, the team, or the budget. It was the architecture.</p>
    <!-- Hero stats -->
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:16px;margin-top:2rem;" class="md-grid-3">
      <div style="text-align:center;background:rgba(18,23,43,0.036);border:1px solid rgba(18,23,43,0.064);border-radius:16px;padding:28px;">
        <div style="font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:900;color:#05C793;margin-bottom:8px;">+35%</div>
        <div style="color:#5B6478;font-size:0.85rem;">Pipeline lead growth</div>
      </div>
      <div style="text-align:center;background:rgba(18,23,43,0.036);border:1px solid rgba(18,23,43,0.064);border-radius:16px;padding:28px;">
        <div style="font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:900;color:#a855f7;margin-bottom:8px;">+25%</div>
        <div style="color:#5B6478;font-size:0.85rem;">Revenue ROI improvement</div>
      </div>
      <div style="text-align:center;background:rgba(18,23,43,0.036);border:1px solid rgba(18,23,43,0.064);border-radius:16px;padding:28px;">
        <div style="font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:900;color:#60a5fa;margin-bottom:8px;">$1.2M</div>
        <div style="color:#5B6478;font-size:0.85rem;">Attributable pipeline impact</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Challenge -->
<section style="padding:60px 0;background:#FFFFFF;">
  <div style="max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 24px;">
    <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:800;color:#12172B;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">The Challenge</h2>
    <p style="color:#5B6478;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem;">A rapidly scaling cybersecurity SaaS firm needed to grow pipeline across MEA and APAC simultaneously. Aggressive targets. Lean team. Strong product. The issue was not any of those things.</p>
    <p style="color:#5B6478;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem;">AI initiatives were running in silos — each region generating its own signals, chasing its own accounts, reporting its own metrics. There was no unified intelligence layer. No shared picture of where buying intent was concentrating. Lead quality was inconsistent. Enterprise conversion was below target. The question from leadership every quarter was the same: why isn't the pipeline growing faster?</p>
    <p style="color:#5B6478;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.8;">The answer was architecture. Disconnected AI initiatives do not compound. They produce data in parallel streams that never talk to each other — and the business optimises for nothing in particular as a result.</p>
    <!-- Problem callout -->
    <div style="margin-top:2rem;display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:16px;" class="md-grid-3">
      <div style="background:rgba(18,23,43,0.029);border:1px solid rgba(255,59,59,0.15);border-radius:14px;padding:20px;">
        <div style="font-size:0.7rem;font-weight:800;color:#f87171;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;margin-bottom:8px;">Problem 01</div>
        <div style="font-size:0.9rem;font-weight:700;color:#12172B;margin-bottom:6px;">No shared intelligence layer</div>
        <div style="font-size:0.83rem;color:#5B6478;line-height:1.6;">Each region produced its own data. No unified view of which accounts were in-market, which channels were generating real intent, or which messages were resonating.</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:rgba(18,23,43,0.029);border:1px solid rgba(255,59,59,0.15);border-radius:14px;padding:20px;">
        <div style="font-size:0.7rem;font-weight:800;color:#f87171;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;margin-bottom:8px;">Problem 02</div>
        <div style="font-size:0.9rem;font-weight:700;color:#12172B;margin-bottom:6px;">Enterprise conversion stuck</div>
        <div style="font-size:0.83rem;color:#5B6478;line-height:1.6;">High-value accounts were being pursued by instinct rather than evidence. Without AI-driven fit scoring, the right accounts weren't getting the right attention at the right time.</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:rgba(18,23,43,0.029);border:1px solid rgba(255,59,59,0.15);border-radius:14px;padding:20px;">
        <div style="font-size:0.7rem;font-weight:800;color:#f87171;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;margin-bottom:8px;">Problem 03</div>
        <div style="font-size:0.9rem;font-weight:700;color:#12172B;margin-bottom:6px;">No revenue attribution</div>
        <div style="font-size:0.83rem;color:#5B6478;line-height:1.6;">Marketing activity couldn't be connected to pipeline outcomes. Leadership couldn't see what was working — so budget decisions were made on activity volume, not revenue evidence.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Approach -->
<section style="padding:60px 0;background:#F7F9FC;">
  <div style="max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 24px;">
    <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:800;color:#12172B;margin-bottom:2rem;">Our Approach</h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:20px;" class="md-grid-3">
      <div style="background:rgba(18,23,43,0.029);border:1px solid rgba(18,23,43,0.064);border-radius:16px;padding:28px;position:relative;">
        <div style="font-size:3rem;font-weight:900;color:#05C793;opacity:0.2;line-height:1;margin-bottom:1rem;">01</div>
        <h4 style="font-size:1.05rem;font-weight:800;color:#12172B;margin-bottom:0.6rem;">AI Strategy Audit</h4>
        <p style="color:#5B6478;font-size:0.88rem;line-height:1.7;">Full diagnostic across both regions — not just campaign performance, but the underlying data model. What signals were being captured, what was being ignored, where buyer intent was hiding, and why conversion was stalling at enterprise tier. We identified the AI gaps, not just the marketing gaps.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:rgba(18,23,43,0.029);border:1px solid rgba(18,23,43,0.064);border-radius:16px;padding:28px;position:relative;">
        <div style="font-size:3rem;font-weight:900;color:#a855f7;opacity:0.2;line-height:1;margin-bottom:1rem;">02</div>
        <h4 style="font-size:1.05rem;font-weight:800;color:#12172B;margin-bottom:0.6rem;">Unified AI Revenue Strategy</h4>
        <p style="color:#5B6478;font-size:0.88rem;line-height:1.7;">Built a single AI strategy across MEA and APAC — replacing isolated regional initiatives with one connected intelligence framework. AI-driven ICP modelling, predictive account scoring, and real-time intent signal aggregation gave both teams a unified picture of which accounts to prioritise and why.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:rgba(18,23,43,0.029);border:1px solid rgba(18,23,43,0.064);border-radius:16px;padding:28px;position:relative;">
        <div style="font-size:3rem;font-weight:900;color:#60a5fa;opacity:0.2;line-height:1;margin-bottom:1rem;">03</div>
        <h4 style="font-size:1.05rem;font-weight:800;color:#12172B;margin-bottom:0.6rem;">AI-Powered ABM &amp; Attribution</h4>
        <p style="color:#5B6478;font-size:0.88rem;line-height:1.7;">Deployed AI-assisted account-based plays targeting enterprise accounts by modelled fit and real-time intent — not manual guesswork. Built full revenue attribution infrastructure from day one, connecting every channel touchpoint to pipeline outcomes and making ROI visible and reportable to leadership.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Solution -->
<section style="padding:60px 0;background:#FFFFFF;">
  <div style="max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 24px;">
    <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:800;color:#12172B;margin-bottom:2rem;">The Solution</h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:32px;align-items:start;" class="md-grid-2">
      <div>
        <p style="color:#5B6478;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem;">We replaced two parallel regional programmes with a single AI strategy operating from one intelligence layer. Rather than two teams optimising separately, we built one connected system — with AI doing the work of identifying which accounts were in-market, which channels were generating real buying signals, and which messages were landing with enterprise decision-makers across both regions.</p>
        <p style="color:#5B6478;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:1rem;">The result was a compounding revenue system. Each cycle generated better data, sharper targeting, and higher-quality pipeline than the one before it. For the first time, sales and marketing were operating from the same AI-generated picture of the market.</p>
        <p style="color:#5B6478;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.8;">Attribution was not a reporting afterthought — it was built into the architecture from day one. Leadership could see exactly what the AI strategy was returning at every stage of the funnel.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="background:rgba(5,199,147,0.04);border:1px solid rgba(5,199,147,0.15);border-radius:16px;padding:28px;">
        <h4 style="font-size:0.9rem;font-weight:800;color:#05C793;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">What Was Delivered</h4>
        <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0;">
          <li style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:10px;color:#374050;font-size:0.88rem;margin-bottom:10px;"><span style="color:#05C793;flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px;">✓</span>Unified AI revenue strategy across MEA &amp; APAC</li>
          <li style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:10px;color:#374050;font-size:0.88rem;margin-bottom:10px;"><span style="color:#05C793;flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px;">✓</span>AI-driven ICP modelling &amp; predictive account scoring</li>
          <li style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:10px;color:#374050;font-size:0.88rem;margin-bottom:10px;"><span style="color:#05C793;flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px;">✓</span>Real-time intent signal aggregation &amp; account prioritisation</li>
          <li style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:10px;color:#374050;font-size:0.88rem;margin-bottom:10px;"><span style="color:#05C793;flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px;">✓</span>AI-assisted ABM program targeting enterprise accounts</li>
          <li style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:10px;color:#374050;font-size:0.88rem;margin-bottom:10px;"><span style="color:#05C793;flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px;">✓</span>Full revenue attribution infrastructure</li>
          <li style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:10px;color:#374050;font-size:0.88rem;margin-bottom:10px;"><span style="color:#05C793;flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px;">✓</span>Executive AI performance dashboard &amp; monthly reporting</li>
        </ul>
