<!-- Key Takeaways -->
<section style="padding:60px 0;background:#FFFFFF;">
  <div style="max-width:900px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 24px;">
    <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem;font-weight:800;color:#12172B;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Key Takeaways</h2>
    <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;margin:0;">
      <li style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:12px;color:#374050;font-size:0.92rem;margin-bottom:18px;line-height:1.75;"><span style="color:#05C793;font-size:1.1rem;flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px;">→</span><span><strong style="color:#12172B;">Disconnected AI initiatives do not compound.</strong> A unified intelligence layer gets smarter with every cycle. Two parallel programmes with no shared data layer never will — no matter how much is invested in either.</span></li>
      <li style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:12px;color:#374050;font-size:0.92rem;margin-bottom:18px;line-height:1.75;"><span style="color:#05C793;font-size:1.1rem;flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px;">→</span><span><strong style="color:#12172B;">The pipeline problem was a data problem.</strong> Without AI-driven ICP modelling and intent signals, the team was targeting accounts by instinct rather than evidence. AI strategy replaced guesswork with precision — and enterprise conversion followed.</span></li>
      <li style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:12px;color:#374050;font-size:0.92rem;margin-bottom:18px;line-height:1.75;"><span style="color:#05C793;font-size:1.1rem;flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px;">→</span><span><strong style="color:#12172B;">Attribution is a strategy deliverable, not a reporting function.</strong> Building revenue attribution into the architecture from day one meant leadership could see exactly what the AI investment was returning — and invest further with confidence.</span></li>
      <li style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:12px;color:#374050;font-size:0.92rem;line-height:1.75;"><span style="color:#05C793;font-size:1.1rem;flex-shrink:0;margin-top:1px;">→</span><span><strong style="color:#12172B;">The $1.2M is not the ceiling.</strong> A compounding AI strategy produces better results with every cycle as the intelligence layer learns. The organisations that unify early set a base the fragmented ones cannot catch up to.</span></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

